A few favorite pics of myself from the @revolve #winterland event last night ❄️✨

I realized I never gave a Debbie and Mary update, so better late than never:

We went to Fred’s on the Upper West Side, it’s a cozy neighborhood spot with the best Brussel sprouts in the city. If you haven’t been, I highly recommend. 

Mary gave me an update on her life: she went from reading to cats to reading to dogs and told me she loves a Guinness at night. She’s also getting her kitchen redone so she’s been spending tons of time at Debbie’s next door. 

Debbie’s a big bird watcher (so was my grandma) and said there’s an owl she’s been watching for nearly a year. She loves to ride the bus so it makes sense that we’re best friends. 

Mary asked me about my love life and I said, “I dunno they say it happens when you least expect it”, her response, “Eh, I haven’t been expecting it for 50 years and I’m still single so don’t listen to that rule.” 🥲

Debbie loves instagram. So much that she literally posts more from Central Park than me and we all know that’s very hard to do. 

I want to get them something for Christmas, Debbie mentioned drinking tea often and Mary…well, she’s a wildcard…help!
